  "A bicycle wheel has a radius of 35 cm. If it makes 10 complete revolutions, what total distance does a point on the rim travel?": "",
  "70pi cm": "",
  "700pi cm": "",
  "1400pi cm": "",
  "350pi cm": "",
  "Each revolution covers an arc of 2pi * r = 2pi * 35 = 70pi cm. For 10 revolutions: 10 * 70pi = 700pi cm, which is approximately 2199 cm or 22 meters.": "",
  "An airplane propeller has blades 1.5 meters long and spins at a rate where one blade sweeps through 3pi/2 radians in one second. What arc length does the tip of the blade trace in one second?": "",
  "4.5pi meters": "",
  "9pi/4 meters": "",
  "3pi meters": "",
  "3pi/2 meters": "",
  "Arc length s = r * theta = 1.5 * (3pi/2) = 4.5pi/2 = 9pi/4 meters, which is approximately 7.07 meters per second.": "",
  "A windshield wiper is 18 inches long and sweeps through an angle of 110 degrees. What is the area of the windshield cleaned by the wiper?": "",
  "162pi square inches": "",
  "99pi square inches": "",
  "55pi square inches": "",
  "198pi square inches": "",
  "Convert 110 degrees to radians: 110 * pi/180 = 11pi/18. Sector area = (1/2)(18^2)(11pi/18) = (1/2)(324)(11pi/18) = (324 * 11pi) / 36 = 3564pi/36 = 99pi square inches.": "",
  "A runner on a circular track with radius 50 meters runs from one point to another, subtending a central angle of 144 degrees. How far did the runner travel along the track?": "",
  "25pi meters": "",
  "40pi meters": "",
  "50pi meters": "",
  "80pi meters": "",
  "Convert 144 degrees to radians: 144 * pi/180 = 4pi/5. Arc length s = 50 * (4pi/5) = 200pi/5 = 40pi meters, which is approximately 125.7 meters.": "",
  "A security camera rotates back and forth through an angle of 240 degrees. If the camera can detect motion within a range of 30 meters, what is the total area the camera monitors?": "",
  "900pi square meters": "",
